word_group.brief_definition: 几乎不了解；难以理解；勉强懂

bilingual.target: 她在会议上几乎不说话。

bilingual.source: He barely managed to catch the last train.
bilingual.target: 他几乎不能赶上最后一班火车。

bilingual.source: The stain on your shirt is barely visible.
bilingual.target: 你衬衫上的污渍几乎不可见。

bilingual.source: Her savings are very meagre, barely enough.
bilingual.target: 她的储蓄非常微薄，几乎不够用。

bilingual.source: The plant barely survived the harsh winter.
bilingual.target: 这株植物在严冬中几乎不能存活。

bilingual.source: He was barely conscious when they found him.
bilingual.target: 他们找到他时，他几乎不清醒。

bilingual.source: They barely had enough money to pay the rent.
bilingual.target: 他们几乎不够钱付房租。

bilingual.source: The pattern on the fabric is barely discernable.
bilingual.target: 布料上的图案几乎不可辨别。

bilingual.source: He wore a tattered jacket that barely kept him warm.
bilingual.target: 他穿着一件破烂的夹克，几乎不能保暖。

yingyinNormal.en: She just eats like a bird, she barely leaves the house.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她吃饭跟小鸟啄食一样，也几乎不出门。

yingyinNormal.en: His search for consciousness consumed him totally. Barely spoke to anyone, except the hosts.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他对意识的探究耗尽了他的生命力，除了接待员，他几乎不和任何人说话。

yingyinNormal.en: Sam Nguyen was my high school janitor. He was an immigrant from Vietnam who barely spoke a word of English.
yingyinNormal.zh: 山姆·阮是我高中里的保卫人员，他是越南移民，他几乎不说英语。

yingyinNormal.en: And I had no idea that something I did could mean more than ever imagined to an immigrant from Vietnam who barely even spoke English.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我以前不知道我所做的对于一个几乎不说英语的越南人能发挥如此超乎我想象的作用。

yingyinNormal.en: I barely left the stratosphere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我也就到过平流层。

yingyinNormal.en: And I barely see you anyway. Yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 即使我几乎没怎么见到过你。是的。

yingyinNormal.en: He's barely ticking. We fear you are too late.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他的心跳很微弱。只怕你来得太晚了。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《爱丽丝梦游仙境2：镜中奇遇记》

yingyinNormal.en: Don't be so melodramatic. You were barely dead.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别这么夸张行不行，你差点死了。

yingyinNormal.en: But to lose Simba, who had barely begun to live.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是辛巴几乎才开始他的生命，竟然也...

yingyinNormal.en: Well, how is that possible? You barely know her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 怎么可能？你们根本不熟。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh for god's sake, I barely touched you. How man are...
yingyinNormal.zh: 看在上帝的份上，我几乎没碰你，这人怎么……

yingyinNormal.en: So I barely had enough pieces of parents to make one whole one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我根本得不到父母的爱。

yingyinNormal.en: Sweetie, you can't possibly remember that. You were barely a year old.
yingyinNormal.zh: 宝贝，你不可能记得的，当时你还不满一岁。

yingyinNormal.en: You didn't know me before I went away. I barely got back into Constance.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不了解我失踪前的我，好不容易回到康士坦次。

yingyinNormal.en: Any kid would be so happy to have these, and you barely even touched them.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有这么多玩具每个小孩都会很开心的，而你却碰都不碰它们。

yingyinNormal.en: She's not letting me in. I'm barely holding on. I'm not strong enough yet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她不让我读心，我勉强才控制住，我还不够强大。

yingyinNormal.en: Ross, that was not a near-death experience. That was barely an experience.
yingyinNormal.zh: 罗斯，那不是濒死经验，就连经验都谈不上了。

yingyinNormal.en: But just barely, and I've been talking about myself all night long. I'm sorry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真是有惊无险，我整晚都在谈我自己，抱歉。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, you barely looked. Let me see. No, no, no, I looked, and no more tickets.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你都没有细看，让我看看。不不不，我看了，没有点券了。

yingyinNormal.en: I didn't trust them. I trust you. Now why would you trust us? You barely know us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不信任他们，我信任你们。你为什么相信我们？你又不认识我们。
